    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I just ran into this bug with gRPC 1.3.2.  The service implementation happens to use Boost serialization routines, which throw exceptions when they encounter an error.  If the service method itself doesn't catch the exception, gRPC core dumps with the above-mentioned `double free or corruption` error.  Even if the service method just does a `throw 0;` the problem manifests."
